30/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The outgoing government on Monday (29 November) approved the future deployment of Macedonian soldiers to the international peacekeeping mission in Iraq. 
Cabinet spokesman Saso Colakovski says the 32-man contingent would come from the army's specialised operations unit. 
The soldiers would be deployed from December 2004 until June 2005. 
The decision must now be approved by parliament.
In other news, the US Embassy in Skopje reopened Tuesday after being closed the previous day for security reasons. 
Officials cited "a potential threat" to the embassy and other US government facilities in Macedonia. 
(A1 TV, Makfax - 30/11/04; Macedonian Government Web site, A1 TV, AFP, AP, UPS - 29/11/04)
